paragraphs.title: Hyperparameters for Artificial Neural Network
paragraphs.text:
val hiddenNeurons = z.input("hiddenNeurons", 700).toString.toDouble.intValue()
val iterations = z.input("iterations", 200).toString.toDouble.intValue()

paragraphs.title: Create an ANN model
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.MultilayerPerceptronClassifier

val layers = Array[Int](500, hiddenNeurons, 2)

val trainer = new MultilayerPerceptronClassifier()
  .setLayers(layers)
  .setSeed(1234L)
  .setMaxIter(iterations)

val model = trainer.fit(train)

paragraphs.title: Model Performance Evaluation
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.MulticlassClassificationEvaluator import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.MulticlassMetrics import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.BinaryClassificationMetrics import org.apache.spark.rdd.RDD val result = model.transform(test) val predictionAndLabels = result.select("prediction", "label") val evaluator = new MulticlassClassificationEvaluator().setMetricName("accuracy") val predictionAndLabelsRDD = predictionAndLabels.map(row => (row.getDouble(0), row.getDouble(1))).rdd val metrics = new MulticlassMetrics(predictionAndLabelsRDD) val binaryMetrics = new BinaryClassificationMetrics(predictionAndLabelsRDD) val cfm = metrics.confusionMatrix val tn = cfm(0, 0) val fp = cfm(0, 1) val fn = cfm(1, 0) val tp = cfm(1, 1) val fpr = fp / (fp + tn) val tpr = tp / (tp + fn) val auc = binaryMetrics.areaUnderROC val precision = evaluator.evaluate(predictionAndLabels) println(s"""%angular

Confusion Matrix

Actual spam Actual ham
Predicted spam ${tn.toInt} ${fn.toInt}
Predicted ham ${fp.toInt} ${tp.toInt}
""".stripMargin) println(s"""%angular

Performance Metrics

False Positive Rate (FPR) ${(fpr * 100).toInt}% ($fpr)
True Positive Rate (TPR) ${(tpr * 100).toInt}% ($tpr)
Area under the ROC ${(auc * 100).toInt}% ($auc)
Precision ${(precision * 100).toInt}% ($precision)
""".stripMargin)

paragraphs.title: Make predictions on new text
paragraphs.text: import sqlContext.implicits._ import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.{HashingTF, Tokenizer} import org.apache.spark.sql.Row val inputText = z.input("sentence", "winner as a valued network customer you have been selected to receivea normalizedcurrencysymbol normalizednumber prize reward to claim call normalizednumber claim code kl normalizednumber valid normalizednumber hours only").toString() val inputDF = sqlContext.createDataFrame(Seq( inputText.split(" ") ).map(Tuple1.apply)).toDF("text") val featurizedData = new HashingTF().setInputCol("text").setOutputCol("features").setNumFeatures(500).transform(inputDF) model.transform(featurizedData).select("features", "prediction").take(1).foreach { case Row(features, prediction) => print(s"""%angular predicted as HAM" else "danger'>SPAM"} """) }
